    Grassrootz API v1

    Scroll down for code samples, example requests and responses. Select a language for code samples from the tabs above or the mobile navigation menu.

    Base URLs:

    • //api.dev.grassrootz.com/

    Authentication

    • API Key (ApiKeyHeader)

      • Parameter Name: ApiKey, in: header. Application API Key

    • API Key (SessionKeyQuery)

      • Parameter Name: Authorization, in: header. Authorization Token

    AccessKey

    ApiV2AccessKeyByIdGet

    Code samples

    # You can also use wget
curl -X GET //api.dev.grassrootz.com//api/v2/AccessKey/{id} \
  -H 'Accept: application/json' \
  -H 'ApiKey: API_KEY'


    GET //api.dev.grassrootz.com//api/v2/AccessKey/{id} HTTP/1.1
Host: null

Accept: application/json


    var headers = {
  'Accept':'application/json',
  'ApiKey':'API_KEY'

};

$.ajax({
  url: '//api.dev.grassrootz.com//api/v2/AccessKey/{id}',
  method: 'get',

  headers: headers,
  success: function(data) {
    console.log(JSON.stringify(data));
  }
})


    const request = require('node-fetch');

const headers = {
  'Accept':'application/json',
  'ApiKey':'API_KEY'

};

fetch('//api.dev.grassrootz.com//api/v2/AccessKey/{id}',
{
  method: 'GET',

  headers: headers
})
.then(function(res) {
    return res.json();
}).then(function(body) {
    console.log(body);
});

  params: {
  }, headers: headers

p JSON.parse(result)

    URL obj = new URL("//api.dev.grassrootz.com//api/v2/AccessKey/{id}");
HttpURLConnection con = (HttpURLConnection) obj.openConnection();
con.setRequestMethod("GET");
int responseCode = con.getResponseCode();
BufferedReader in = new BufferedReader(
    new InputStreamReader(con.getInputStream()));
String inputLine;
StringBuffer response = new StringBuffer();
while ((inputLine = in.readLine()) != null) {
    response.append(inputLine);
}
in.close();
System.out.println(response.toString());


    package main

import (
       "bytes"
       "net/http"
)

func main() {

    headers := map[string][]string{
        "Accept": []string{"application/json"},
        "ApiKey": []string{"API_KEY"},

    }

    data := bytes.NewBuffer([]byte{jsonReq})
    req, err := http.NewRequest("GET", "//api.dev.grassrootz.com//api/v2/AccessKey/{id}", data)
    req.Header = headers

    client := &http.Client{}
    resp, err := client.Do(req)
    // ...
}

    GET /api/v2/AccessKey/{id}

    Gets a key object by id

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    id path integer(int32) true Donation id

    Example responses

    200 Response

    {
  "data": {
    "organizationId": 0,
    "organization": {
      "id": 0,
      "name": "string",
      "urlPath": "string"
    },
    "clientKey": "string",
    "description": "string",
    "createdAt": "2018-08-20T06:00:18Z"
  },
  "success": true,
  "error": [
    {
      "error": "string",
      "param": "string"
    }
  ]
}

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Success ScalarActionResult_AccessKeyElementModel_
    400 Bad Request Bad Request ScalarActionResult_AccessKeyElementModel_
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated by means of one of the following methods: ApiKeyHeader & None

    req.Header = headers

    client := &http.Client{}
    resp, err := client.Do(req)
    // ...
}

    PUT /api/v2/AccessKey/{id}

    Updates a donation key by id

    Body parameter

    {
  "organizationId": 0,
  "description": "string"
}

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    id path integer(int32) true The id of the donation object being modified
    body body AccessKeyEditModel false The donation model containing the changes

    Example responses

    200 Response

    {
  "data": {
    "organizationId": 0,
    "organization": {
      "id": 0,
      "name": "string",
      "urlPath": "string"
    },
    "clientKey": "string",
    "description": "string",
    "createdAt": "2018-08-20T06:00:18Z"
  },
  "success": true,
  "error": [
    {
      "error": "string",
      "param": "string"
    }
  ]
}

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Success ScalarActionResult_AccessKeyElementModel_
    400 Bad Request Bad Request ScalarActionResult_AccessKeyElementModel_
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated by means of one of the following methods: ApiKeyHeader & None

      "param": "string"

  ]

    package main

import (
       "bytes"
       "net/http"
)

func main() {

    headers := map[string][]string{
        "Content-Type": []string{"application/json-patch+json"},
        "Accept": []string{"application/json"},
        "ApiKey": []string{"API_KEY"},

    }

    data := bytes.NewBuffer([]byte{jsonReq})
    req, err := http.NewRequest("PATCH", "//api.dev.grassrootz.com//api/v2/AccessKey/{id}", data)
    req.Header = headers

    "key": "string",

    GET /api/v2/Account/aggregate

    Perform an aggregate function on a field based on a filter/custom-text criteria

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    fieldName query string false none
    fieldAggregate query string false none
    filters query array[any] false none
    text query string false none
    orderBy.key query string false none
    orderBy.direction query string false none
    page query integer(int32) false none
    pageSize query integer(int32) false none
    resultType query string false none
    includeDataTemplate query boolean false none

    Enumerated Values

    Parameter Value
    fieldAggregate sum
    fieldAggregate average
    fieldAggregate min
    fieldAggregate max
    fieldAggregate count
    orderBy.direction asc
    orderBy.direction desc
    resultType lookup
    resultType basic
    resultType full

    GET /api/v2/account/donor/aggregate

    Perform an aggregate function on a field based on a filter/custom-text criteria

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    fieldName query string false none
    fieldAggregate query string false none
    filters query array[any] false none
    text query string false none
    orderBy.key query string false none
    orderBy.direction query string false none
    page query integer(int32) false none
    pageSize query integer(int32) false none
    resultType query string false none
    includeDataTemplate query boolean false none

    Enumerated Values

    Parameter Value
    fieldAggregate sum
    fieldAggregate average
    fieldAggregate min
    fieldAggregate max
    fieldAggregate count
    orderBy.direction asc
    orderBy.direction desc
    resultType lookup
    resultType basic
    resultType full

    Example responses

  "success": true,
  "error": [
    {
      "error": "string",
      "param": "string"
    }
  ]

con.setRequestMethod("GET");

}
in.close();

    req.Header = headers

    client := &http.Client{}
    resp, err := client.Do(req)
    // ...
}

    page query integer(int32) false none

    includeDataTemplate query boolean false none

    Creates a new donation message reply

    Body parameter

    {
  "reply": "string"
}

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    id path integer(int32) true The donation id being replied to
    body body DonationMessageReplyEditModel false The donation model containing the details

    Example responses

  "error": [

    package main

)

    headers := map[string][]string{
        "Content-Type": []string{"application/json-patch+json"},
        "Accept": []string{"application/json"},
        "ApiKey": []string{"API_KEY"},

    }

    data := bytes.NewBuffer([]byte{jsonReq})
    req, err := http.NewRequest("POST", "//api.dev.grassrootz.com//api/v2/DonationFee", data)
    req.Header = headers

    client := &http.Client{}
    resp, err := client.Do(req)
    // ...
}

    Search (list request) of a set of objects based on a list of filters, text, paging and ordering parameters

    Body parameter

    {

    {
      "key": "string",
      "operator": "equalTo",
      "value": "string"
    }
  ],
  "text": "string",
  "orderBy": {
    "key": "string",
    "direction": "asc"
  },
  "page": 0,
  "pageSize": 0,
  "resultType": "lookup",
  "includeDataTemplate": true
}

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    body body DonationFeeSearchModel false Implements ISearching and offers custom filters, text matching, paging and ordering

    GET /api/v2/DonationFee/metadata

    Returns a list of filters that can be implemented and work nicely with /search

    Example responses

    200 Response

    {
  "data": {
    "columns": [
      {
        "key": "string",
        "dataType": "string",
        "additionalData": {}
      }
    ],
    "filters": [

    GET /api/v2/page/Event/aggregate

    Perform an aggregate function on a field based on a filter/custom-text criteria

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    fieldName query string false none
    fieldAggregate query string false none
    filters query array[any] false none
    text query string false none
    orderBy.key query string false none
    orderBy.direction query string false none
    page query integer(int32) false none
    pageSize query integer(int32) false none
    resultType query string false none
    includeDataTemplate query boolean false none

    Enumerated Values

    Parameter Value
    fieldAggregate sum
    fieldAggregate average
    fieldAggregate min
    fieldAggregate max
    fieldAggregate count
    orderBy.direction asc
    orderBy.direction desc
    resultType lookup
    resultType basic
    resultType full

    pageSize query integer(int32) false none
    resultType query string false none
    includeDataTemplate query boolean false none

    POST /api/v2/Page/search

    {
      "key": "string",
      "operator": "equalTo",
      "value": "string"

    "key": "string",
    "direction": "asc"
  },
  "page": 0,
  "pageSize": 0,
  "resultType": "lookup",
  "includeDataTemplate": true
}

    GET /api/v2/Page/aggregate

    Perform an aggregate function on a field based on a filter/custom-text criteria

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    fieldName query string false none
    fieldAggregate query string false none
    filters query array[any] false none
    text query string false none
    orderBy.key query string false none
    orderBy.direction query string false none
    page query integer(int32) false none
    pageSize query integer(int32) false none
    resultType query string false none
    includeDataTemplate query boolean false none

    Enumerated Values

    Parameter Value
    fieldAggregate sum
    fieldAggregate average
    fieldAggregate min
    fieldAggregate max
    fieldAggregate count
    orderBy.direction asc
    orderBy.direction desc
    resultType lookup
    resultType basic
    resultType full

    Example responses

  "success": true,
